org.matsim.core.utils.collections

Class PseudoRemovePriorityQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.core.utils.collections.PseudoRemovePriorityQueue<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements held in this collection
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, RouterPriorityQueue<E>

    public class PseudoRemovePriorityQueue<E>
extends Object
implements RouterPriorityQueue<E>
    A simple re-implementation of a priority queue that offers a much better performance for remove operations than the standard PriorityQueue, but uses more memory to manage the data.
    The actual implementation is backed by a standard PriorityQueue. Each added object is encapsulated in a simple structure together with a valid-flag. If an element should be removed, the valid-flag is invalidated but the element remains in the collection, foregoing the expensive linear remove operation from the standard PriorityQueue implementation. Polling for elements makes sure only valid elements are returned, all others are just ignored.
    Author:
    mrieser
    See Also:
    PriorityQueue
